history.text: Hi, have you seen the movie Iron Man with Robert Downey, Jr?
Yes I have!
What was your favorite part in that movie
I thought it had the greatest special effects.
Probably when he uses his original iron man suite to escape the terrorists at the beginning. What about you?
the special effects were very good for the time but now they seem a bit outdated
I think my favorite part was when he was in that cave prison and first had his power heart made
yes, it was very interesting! It shows a lot for his character!
Did you like his character?
Yeah, I think he played the character really well.
He played a very smart and rich man LOL
True. Though I do not think I would want to meet him in real life. What about you?
I loved Terrence Howard as his sort of side kick
yes, he was very good!
I really think that the actors they decided on for this movie were great.
yes, all of the marvel casting choices were very well thought out.
Would you watch again
Probably, especially with the new avengers movie coming out, it would be good to catch up on it
hahaha, I do that too. I usually watch the first movies before the new ones come out just to keep in sync.
yeah, it has been a long time since I have seen it. Do you like the 2nd iron man?
I enjoyed the scene at the charity even where that reporter informs Stark that his company's weapons were being used for a bad way
I like them all
Yes, he was unaware of  his negative actions on the world. Which is your favourite one?
The first one, I think. The others are good and I like them, but the first movies are usually always the best.
very true. It was very cool and original when it first came out!
Makes you wonder with the king of technology that they showed in this movie, how much of that is really possible?
well a bunch of it has come about since teh 10 years have passed since the movie came out, like touch screens and intelligent robots
The part where that one guy (can't remember his name) but when he stole Stark's arc reactor that was keeping him alive, that was tense
yes, it was at the climax of the movie, though I knew it would all work out in the end
Yeah, never thought he would admit to the public that he was Iron Man
well it makes sense though, no point in hiding it lol!
yeah, but you have to admit, most superheroes hide their identities
yeah like batman. but I think iron man is full of him self more them most super heros, he probably wants the recognition!
That's true, he truly was a head case LOL

uid1response.feedback: The movie sounds more interesting now that I have discussed it. There were alot of parts I forgot
